title: KEEP UP

description.plain:
“KEEP UP” replicates the style of Odetari’s older glitch-style EDM songs, notably imitating the lyrics and production of “YOU’RE TOO SLOW”, one of his older mainstream songs.

This song came around when Odetari set up a vote on SoundCloud with a playlist titled “PICK THE NEXT SINGLE TO DROP” for which of two songs he should release first, between “FROSTBITE” and “KEEP UP”, with the latter supposedly winning. While “FROSTBITE” had been previously previewed on TikTok prior to the vote, “KEEP UP” had little to no mention from Odetari. Around a month after the vote started, Odetari stated on the caption of a TikTok that he would be releasing both of the songs together, stating:

I originally made this song for some special but you all voted, and i decided i’m dropping KEEP UP AND FROSTBITE TOGETHER ❤️

He still kept the vote in mind, however, as the advertising for the 2-song single was mainly focused on the supposed winner, “KEEP UP”. In addition, the lyrics and the theme of the song was a huge inspiration of the video game hedgehog character, Sonic.
